<script language=javascript>
 function checkall(checkbox, prefix) {
     for (var i = 0; i < checkbox.form.elements.length ; i++) {
        var e = checkbox.form.elements[i];
        if (e.name && e.name.indexOf(prefix) == 0) {
           e.checked = checkbox.checked;
        }
     }
  }

</script>

<div class=dark-bar>Submit Krang Bug</div>
<form name="bug_form" method="post">
<table cellspacing="0" width="100%">
<tr class="form-cell">
<td class="form-cell"><b> Summary</b> </td><td class="form-cell"><input type="text" size="60" name="summary" id="short_desc"><p>
        A sentence which summarizes the problem.
        Please be descriptive and use lots of keywords.
      </p> 
<p>
        <tt>
          <font color="#990000">Bad example</font>: krang crashed when in story.
        </tt>

        <br>
        <tt>
          <font color="#009900">Good example</font>:
          krang crashed with an internal server error while I was editing story "my story", after adding a contributor and clicking 'save'.
        </tt>
      </p>
    </td> 
</tr>
<tr>
    <td class="form-cell">
      <b>Description</b> 
    </td>
    <td class="form-cell">
<textarea rows="6" cols="60" name="description"
                wrap="hard"></textarea>
      <p>
        Expand on the Summary. Please be
        as specific as possible about what is wrong.
      </p>
      <p>

        <tt>
          <font color="#990000">Bad example</font>: This page looks wrong in
          Mozilla. Other browsers display it correctly. 
        </tt>
        <br>
        <tt>
          <font color="#009900">Good example</font>: In the
          page at http://www.foo.com/, text in the first column should be
          fully justified -- text should be aligned with both the left and
          right margins. In Mozilla, the text is only left-justified.
        </tt>
      </p>
    </td>
  </tr>

<tr>
    <td class="form-cell">
      <b>Reproducability</b>
    </td>
    <td class="form-cell">
<select name="reproduce">
        <option name="Always" value="Always">
          Every time.
        </option>
        <option name="Sometimes" value="Sometimes">
          Sometimes, but not always.
        </option>
        <option name="DidntTry" value="Didn't try">
                                                                           
          Haven't tried to reproduce it.
        </option>
        <option name="NotReproducible" value="Couldn't Reproduce">
          Tried, but couldn't reproduce it.
        </option>
      </select>
      <p>
        How often can you reproduce the problem?
      </p>
    </td>
  </tr>

<tr>

    <td class="form-cell">
      <b>Steps to Reproduce</b> 
    </td>
    <td class="form-cell">
<textarea rows="4" cols="60" name="steps" wrap="hard">
1.
2.
3.
</textarea>
      <p>
        Describe how to reproduce the problem, step by
        step. Include any special setup steps.
      </p>
    </td>

  </tr>

  <tr> 
    <td class="form-cell">
      <b>Actual Results</b> 
    </td>
<td class="form-cell">
<textarea rows="4" cols="60" name="actual_results"
                wrap="hard"></textarea>
      <p>
        What happened after you performed the steps above?
      </p>  
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td class="form-cell">
      <b>Expected Results</b> 
    </td>
    <td class="form-cell">
<textarea rows="4" cols="60" name="expected_results"
                wrap="hard"></textarea>
      <p>

        What should have Krang done instead?
      </p>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="form-cell">
      <b>Severity</b>
    </td>
    <td class="form-cell">
      <select name="bug_severity">
        <option name="blocker" value="blocker">
          Blocker: This bug prevents you from using Krang.
        </option>
        <option name="critical" value="critical">
          Critical: Krang crashes, hangs, or causes you to 
          lose data.
        </option>
        <option name="major" value="major">
          Major: A major feature is broken.
        </option>
        <option name="normal" value="normal" selected="selected">
          Normal: It's a bug that should be fixed.
        </option>
        <option name="minor" value="minor">
          Minor: Minor loss of function, and there's an easy workaround.
        </option>
        <option name="trivial" value="trivial">
          Trivial: A cosmetic problem, such as a misspelled word or 
          misaligned text.
        </option>
      </select>
    <p>
        How serious is the problem?
      </p>

    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<input type="hidden" name="rm" value="commit" override='1'>
<div class=button-bar>
  <input type=submit value="Submit Bug">
</div>
</form>

<tmpl_include footer.tmpl>
